Articles.Content:
This is approximately the thirty-sixth thread about crashes on 1.3 (I've been keeping track). So far all have been due to out of date mods.

Start over from a completely fresh install, find the newest download of each mod, and only install it if the author specifically labeled it as compatible with 1.3.0. If you install a mod that's only for 1.2.2, your game will crash.
Did the above steps, game is still crashing.

19 minutes ago, Darth C3P0 said:

Did the above steps, game is still crashing.

You missed something; at least one of the mods you installed isn't compatible.

4 hours ago, HebaruSan said:

This is approximately the thirty-sixth thread about crashes on 1.3 (I've been keeping track). So far all have been due to out of date mods.

I'll say this: this subforum has cured me of any insane desire to ever enter the IT field.

To the OP: there was a reason why this thread was stickied, and labeled "READ FIRST".

My suggestion: read it. In the vanishingly slim chance your problem isn't another out-of-date mod, there will be much more informative logs for debugging.

New file, finally figured out what to upload thanks to you.
